WEBVTT

00:00:01.921 --> 00:00:04.383
[footsteps]

00:00:04.467 --> 00:00:07.766
I must say, I didn't expect
those two to end up together.

00:00:09.811 --> 00:00:10.813
-[ARIEL] Oh, my!
-[FITZ gasps]

00:00:11.732 --> 00:00:13.611
♪

00:00:13.694 --> 00:00:16.157
[FITZ] I wonder if Rudy's
tried dating anyone.

00:00:16.449 --> 00:00:18.036
I think he likes girls...

00:00:18.411 --> 00:00:21.084
but maybe
he's taken a vow of abstinence.

00:00:21.459 --> 00:00:22.837
[indistinct chatter outside]

00:00:23.046 --> 00:00:25.259
Can't get too excited
either way.

00:00:25.927 --> 00:00:28.975
After all, he's waving
at his friend, "Master Fitz"

00:00:29.141 --> 00:00:30.143
not at me.

00:00:31.354 --> 00:00:34.360
♪

00:00:34.736 --> 00:00:35.738
[footsteps ascending]

00:00:35.863 --> 00:00:38.536
Turns out,
"Silent" is a girl his age.

00:00:38.828 --> 00:00:41.291
And it's fairly obvious
that he's interested in her.

00:00:42.084 --> 00:00:44.631
The two of them share
some kind of special bond,

00:00:44.715 --> 00:00:46.635
one that I don't
fully understand.

00:00:47.887 --> 00:00:49.891
Whatever it is,
they seem much closer

00:00:49.975 --> 00:00:52.479
than Rudy and I were
back in Buena Village.

00:00:52.689 --> 00:00:54.275
[door creaks shut]

00:00:54.358 --> 00:00:57.364
♪

00:00:59.619 --> 00:01:01.999
She showed up in his in life
out of nowhere.

00:01:02.249 --> 00:01:04.337
They act like they've known
each other forever.

00:01:04.462 --> 00:01:06.925
♪

00:01:07.009 --> 00:01:08.888
Always at each other's side.

00:01:09.806 --> 00:01:10.808
[groans]

00:01:12.687 --> 00:01:13.981
What do I do?

00:01:14.106 --> 00:01:16.152
I'm too scared to make a move.

00:01:18.448 --> 00:01:21.329
How did I just lose
all my nerve?

00:01:23.333 --> 00:01:25.462
I thought
I was braver than this.

00:01:25.672 --> 00:01:27.007
What happened?

00:01:27.216 --> 00:01:28.218
♪

00:03:02.657 --> 00:03:04.410
[RUDEUS] I've been
at the University of Magic

00:03:04.493 --> 00:03:05.495
for about a year.

00:03:05.705 --> 00:03:07.374
Enough time
for me to turn sixteen.

00:03:07.457 --> 00:03:08.459
[swishing]

00:03:08.586 --> 00:03:10.548
I still begin each day
with a workout...

00:03:11.257 --> 00:03:12.510
only new thing about that

00:03:12.594 --> 00:03:14.305
-is some added motivation.
-[BADIGADI grunts]

00:03:15.766 --> 00:03:17.979
[RUDEUS] I never know
how to talk to this guy.

00:03:18.187 --> 00:03:19.566
Still kinda scared of him.

00:03:19.649 --> 00:03:20.693
Tell me.

00:03:20.860 --> 00:03:21.695
Yeah?

00:03:21.778 --> 00:03:23.448
Why do you desire strength?

00:03:23.532 --> 00:03:25.953
I'm not quite sure
how to answer that.

00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:28.333
[BADIGADI] I've known many men
obsessed with the pursuit

00:03:28.416 --> 00:03:30.295
of strength, fame, and fortune.

00:03:30.504 --> 00:03:32.967
Not a decent one among them,
if you ask me!

00:03:33.426 --> 00:03:34.763
All narrow-minded.

00:03:34.846 --> 00:03:37.351
There are more worthwhile
things to chase in life.

00:03:38.144 --> 00:03:39.689
Like what, would you say?

00:03:39.856 --> 00:03:41.359
[BADIGADI]
Like women, boy!

00:03:42.862 --> 00:03:45.367
You'll understand once you find
one for yourself!

00:03:45.492 --> 00:03:48.498
[laughs]

00:03:48.624 --> 00:03:50.293
Speaking of, Your Majesty.

00:03:50.377 --> 00:03:51.295
[BADIGADI]
What is it?

00:03:51.379 --> 00:03:53.884
Do you happen to know
a cure for impotence?

00:03:54.803 --> 00:03:55.971
I do not.

00:03:56.138 --> 00:03:57.182
[sighs]

00:03:59.646 --> 00:04:00.981
[RUDEUS]
After a little training,

00:04:01.065 --> 00:04:03.821
it's time for breakfast
and then on to class.

00:04:04.446 --> 00:04:05.783
[STUDENT 210A]
What a pain in the ass.

00:04:05.866 --> 00:04:07.327
-You're tellin' me.
-[BOTH gasp]

00:04:07.954 --> 00:04:09.373
[STUDENT 210A]
Can you believe this weather?

00:04:09.456 --> 00:04:10.668
[STUDENT 210B]
It's just lovely!

00:04:11.293 --> 00:04:13.507
♪

00:04:13.590 --> 00:04:15.511
[RUDEUS] Since
that "duel" with Badigadi,

00:04:15.594 --> 00:04:17.974
most of the other students
steer clear of me.

00:04:20.730 --> 00:04:22.190
Uh, hey.

00:04:27.242 --> 00:04:28.202
[chuckles]

00:04:28.286 --> 00:04:29.246
Uh.

00:04:29.329 --> 00:04:32.294
Come on, you can cut Goliade
a little bit of slack, boss.

00:04:32.377 --> 00:04:34.298
Her heart's in the right place
and everything.

00:04:34.423 --> 00:04:37.012
Besides, I'd like it if you
tried to make us look good

00:04:37.095 --> 00:04:39.057
in front of the other
beast folk, meow.

00:04:39.141 --> 00:04:41.395
With all the minions
that you have at this point,

00:04:41.479 --> 00:04:43.567
it's gotten tougher
being your number two.

00:04:43.650 --> 00:04:45.988
Hey, meow,
I'm the boss' number two!

00:04:46.072 --> 00:04:48.744
Now, now, there's no need
to argue about it, okay?

00:04:48.869 --> 00:04:51.081
I consider you both
my number two.

00:04:51.373 --> 00:04:52.334
[LINIA sighs]

00:04:52.502 --> 00:04:54.004
Way to miss the point, boss.

00:04:54.088 --> 00:04:56.593
We need a clearly defined
hierarchy.

00:04:56.885 --> 00:04:57.929
Yes we do.

00:04:58.179 --> 00:05:00.141
Like, since you can beat
Silent Fitz.

00:05:00.225 --> 00:05:01.770
You could basically
run this place.

00:05:01.853 --> 00:05:04.316
Me, in charge here?
No, thank you.

00:05:04.399 --> 00:05:06.947
Now, grow a pair and show off
your claws, meow!

00:05:07.030 --> 00:05:08.157
Not happening.

00:05:08.241 --> 00:05:09.201
[Both exclaim]

00:05:09.284 --> 00:05:11.623
[writing on chalk board]

00:05:13.710 --> 00:05:14.712
-[CLIFF] Rudeus.
-[RUDEUS] Hmm?

00:05:15.338 --> 00:05:17.092
What all do you know
about curses?

00:05:17.175 --> 00:05:18.094
-Hmm.
-[RUDEUS] A growing

00:05:18.177 --> 00:05:19.263
interest of his lately.

00:05:19.764 --> 00:05:20.933
[RUDEUS] Curses, huh?

00:05:21.433 --> 00:05:23.145
Curses, curses...

00:05:24.148 --> 00:05:25.108
-Huh!
-Well,

00:05:25.191 --> 00:05:27.279
a friend once told me
that Laplace transferred

00:05:27.362 --> 00:05:28.740
his curse to objects,

00:05:28.949 --> 00:05:31.078
and that let him force
the curse onto others.

00:05:31.161 --> 00:05:32.122
That so?

00:05:32.205 --> 00:05:33.207
Mm-hmm.

00:05:33.416 --> 00:05:36.130
He cursed the spears he gave
the Superd in the Laplace War,

00:05:36.213 --> 00:05:38.719
they didn't use their own.
And, basically,

00:05:38.802 --> 00:05:40.806
it caused them to go on
a bloody rampage,

00:05:40.890 --> 00:05:43.227
which led to their whole race
being vilified.

00:05:43.311 --> 00:05:44.856
-[furniture clattering]
-Seriously?!

00:05:44.981 --> 00:05:46.275
That's how that started?!

00:05:46.358 --> 00:05:47.945
-[JENIUS clears throat]
-[stuttering]

00:05:48.780 --> 00:05:49.782
[both sighing]

00:05:50.450 --> 00:05:51.452
Sounds like.

00:05:51.536 --> 00:05:53.832
Just according
to what I heard, at least.

00:05:54.333 --> 00:05:55.335
Fascinating.

00:05:56.212 --> 00:05:57.840
Transferring a curse.

00:05:57.924 --> 00:06:00.220
♪

00:06:00.303 --> 00:06:01.640
That's very helpful.

00:06:01.806 --> 00:06:03.434
Thanks, Rudeus,
I've got an idea

00:06:03.518 --> 00:06:04.604
on what to do now.

00:06:04.896 --> 00:06:06.315
[JENIUS coughs
and clears throat]

00:06:06.398 --> 00:06:07.400
[both groan]

00:06:07.484 --> 00:06:09.321
[RUDEUS]
After class, it's lunchtime.

00:06:09.446 --> 00:06:12.452
[indistinct chatter]

00:06:12.662 --> 00:06:15.333
-How about we grab a seat
right here? -Good idea,

00:06:15.416 --> 00:06:17.880
as Julie wouldn't be able
to join us on the third floor.

00:06:19.132 --> 00:06:20.678
[STUDENT 210C]
Hey, that's Rudeus!

00:06:20.761 --> 00:06:22.180
Guy's a powerhouse.

00:06:22.347 --> 00:06:25.311
Took down every other special
student in his first year!

00:06:25.478 --> 00:06:27.858
Oh, yeah, not to mention
one-shotting the Demon King

00:06:27.942 --> 00:06:29.529
in front
of literally everybody.

00:06:30.154 --> 00:06:30.906
[RUDEUS]
I don't mind

00:06:30.990 --> 00:06:32.660
getting my ego stroked,
of course,

00:06:32.868 --> 00:06:34.580
but I can't let it go
to my head.

00:06:34.914 --> 00:06:36.584
[BADIGADI guffaws]

00:06:36.668 --> 00:06:38.588
[thudding footsteps] If it
isn't my mighty little friend,

00:06:38.672 --> 00:06:40.425
all tucked away in a corner!

00:06:40.509 --> 00:06:41.803
[laughs]

00:06:41.886 --> 00:06:42.847
[thudding]

00:06:42.930 --> 00:06:44.767
[glugging]

00:06:44.851 --> 00:06:46.020
[sighing]

00:06:46.103 --> 00:06:47.105
Oh.

00:06:48.065 --> 00:06:49.192
Master, that thing

00:06:49.276 --> 00:06:51.656
His Majesty's drinking
looks so yummy.

00:06:51.823 --> 00:06:52.992
[both gulp]

00:06:53.702 --> 00:06:55.204
[laughs]

00:06:55.329 --> 00:06:57.000
Spoken like a true dwarf!

00:06:57.083 --> 00:06:59.881
Incredible that she can discern
quality at such a young age!

00:06:59.964 --> 00:07:01.760
Yes.
You wouldn't be opposed

00:07:01.843 --> 00:07:03.972
to sharing a drop or two
with us, Your Majesty?

00:07:04.097 --> 00:07:05.684
Surely you jest, boy!

00:07:05.768 --> 00:07:07.980
Few things are less fun
than drinking alone!

00:07:08.147 --> 00:07:10.193
-But don't stop at a drop!
-Ah.

00:07:10.318 --> 00:07:13.240
-[BADIGADI] Guzzle away!
-[laughs]

00:07:13.324 --> 00:07:15.579
Yes, this is not a beverage
to be sipped!

00:07:15.954 --> 00:07:18.585
Then maybe it'd be better
to wait until after class.

00:07:18.668 --> 00:07:19.670
[sighs]

00:07:19.921 --> 00:07:20.964
[gulps and sighs loudly]

00:07:21.048 --> 00:07:22.050
[groans]

00:07:22.217 --> 00:07:23.302
-[glugging]
-[JULIETTE] Ah!

00:07:23.385 --> 00:07:25.139
If that's your wish,
I shall obey.

00:07:26.016 --> 00:07:27.227
[loudly laughs]

00:07:27.645 --> 00:07:29.941
It's a tough road
for you scholars, huh?

00:07:30.024 --> 00:07:32.195
♪

00:07:32.278 --> 00:07:33.280
[RUDEUS]
After lunch,

00:07:33.364 --> 00:07:36.120
I retreat to this lab covered
in magic-resistant brick

00:07:36.286 --> 00:07:37.873
for summoning experiments.

00:07:38.959 --> 00:07:40.796
My part in this
isn't too demanding.

00:07:41.213 --> 00:07:43.134
I just pour mana
into magic circles

00:07:43.217 --> 00:07:45.096
that Nanahoshi devised herself.

00:07:45.806 --> 00:07:46.808
[chiming]

00:07:46.891 --> 00:07:48.060
They say most proven

00:07:48.144 --> 00:07:49.730
summoning circles
have been lost.

00:07:50.148 --> 00:07:52.360
But by studying
the principles behind them,

00:07:52.570 --> 00:07:54.322
coupled with
lots of experimentation

00:07:54.406 --> 00:07:56.076
with countless
different circles,

00:07:56.578 --> 00:07:59.291
she's managed to invent a few
of her own original spells.

00:08:00.042 --> 00:08:01.754
Gotta say, I'm very impressed.

00:08:01.880 --> 00:08:02.882
[gasps]

00:08:03.132 --> 00:08:04.134
[puffing]

00:08:09.102 --> 00:08:10.606
Was that a success?

00:08:11.023 --> 00:08:12.610
Nope, another dud.

00:08:13.402 --> 00:08:14.487
[RUDEUS]
Now, with me here,

00:08:14.572 --> 00:08:16.408
she's taking
the "kitchen sink" approach.

00:08:16.743 --> 00:08:18.914
We're testing more circles
than I can count.

00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:24.424
So hey, what is the end goal
of this experiment, exactly?

00:08:24.759 --> 00:08:26.094
[NANAHOSHI]
Eventually I want to summon

00:08:26.178 --> 00:08:27.765
a person from our world.

00:08:28.015 --> 00:08:30.353
But in the short-term,
I'm just trying to work out

00:08:30.436 --> 00:08:32.775
the major principles
on a much smaller scale.

00:08:33.150 --> 00:08:34.612
[RUDEUS]
It shouldn't be possible.

00:08:34.779 --> 00:08:37.116
But if she can draw a circle
that summons a person...

00:08:37.492 --> 00:08:40.414
she should be able to draw one
that sends them back, as well.

00:08:40.707 --> 00:08:42.126
That's the hope, anyway.

00:08:42.836 --> 00:08:43.838
[sighs]

00:08:44.715 --> 00:08:46.051
Let me ask you something...

00:08:46.426 --> 00:08:49.182
Say you do make that happen,
besides getting home

00:08:49.307 --> 00:08:51.604
won't that cause another big
mana disaster?

00:08:52.021 --> 00:08:54.025
[NANAHOSHI] I'm planning
to avoid that, of course.

00:08:54.401 --> 00:08:56.196
If I can prove
a few more theorems,

00:08:56.405 --> 00:08:58.535
I can form a hypothesis
as to why it happened

00:08:58.618 --> 00:08:59.494
in the first place,

00:08:59.578 --> 00:09:01.582
and how to keep it from
happening again.

00:09:01.916 --> 00:09:02.918
[RUDEUS]
Well, they say

00:09:03.002 --> 00:09:05.047
that failure
is a part of experimentation,

00:09:05.131 --> 00:09:08.304
so please don't take the risk
too lightly, okay?

00:09:08.888 --> 00:09:10.099
Obviously.

00:09:10.224 --> 00:09:12.228
Why do you think
I'm starting with the basics?

00:09:12.605 --> 00:09:13.606
[sighs]

00:09:15.109 --> 00:09:18.282
You know, I would love to learn
about summoning magic, myself.

00:09:18.575 --> 00:09:19.785
[NANAHOSHI]
You must understand,

00:09:19.869 --> 00:09:21.413
this knowledge is my lifeline.

00:09:21.496 --> 00:09:23.292
I need to be careful
about sharing it.

00:09:23.417 --> 00:09:25.087
Yeah, but part
of this arrangement

00:09:25.171 --> 00:09:26.507
was that you would share it.

00:09:26.591 --> 00:09:27.885
[NANAHOSHI]
Okay, fine.

00:09:28.010 --> 00:09:30.599
I'll tell you one thing
after this experiment, promise.

00:09:31.559 --> 00:09:32.686
[RUDEUS]
Only one?

00:09:32.936 --> 00:09:34.230
Doesn't seem worth it to me.

00:09:35.274 --> 00:09:36.778
Well, think of it this way,

00:09:36.861 --> 00:09:39.366
as soon as my research is done
and I've gone home,

00:09:39.491 --> 00:09:41.244
you get access
to all my writing.

00:09:41.453 --> 00:09:43.290
I'm sure you can be patient
in the meantime.

00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:44.334
[sighs]

00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:45.336
[RUDEUS]
Ugh,

00:09:45.419 --> 00:09:47.591
I guess begging before
we actually get anything done

00:09:47.674 --> 00:09:48.635
would be pretty pathetic.

00:09:49.052 --> 00:09:50.096
Oomph!

00:09:50.346 --> 00:09:51.599
[NANAHOSHI] If you
wanna know that badly,

00:09:51.682 --> 00:09:53.227
do some research of your own.

00:09:53.561 --> 00:09:55.147
Thanks, I appreciate it.

00:09:55.899 --> 00:09:58.195
♪

00:09:58.278 --> 00:09:59.280
[RUDEUS]
After dinner, I give

00:09:59.364 --> 00:10:00.867
Julie magic lessons.

00:10:00.951 --> 00:10:02.955
♪

00:10:03.038 --> 00:10:04.040
[chuckling]

00:10:05.585 --> 00:10:07.422
And then onto figure making.

00:10:07.506 --> 00:10:09.259
This is still Julie's
first year.

00:10:09.677 --> 00:10:12.014
So her mana capacity
is fairly low,

00:10:12.098 --> 00:10:14.227
and I wouldn't say
she has much finesse.

00:10:14.645 --> 00:10:16.356
I mean, she is good
with her hands,

00:10:16.733 --> 00:10:17.734
but she's only just started

00:10:17.818 --> 00:10:18.945
-using sculpting tools..
-[RUDEUS] Not bad, but...

00:10:19.028 --> 00:10:20.949
...so her skills aren't honed
yet. ...look at this side

00:10:21.032 --> 00:10:21.909
of the face.

00:10:21.993 --> 00:10:24.080
[RUDEUS] We've gotta think
in the long term.

00:10:24.289 --> 00:10:27.003
♪

00:10:31.261 --> 00:10:32.639
Since I met Nanahoshi,

00:10:33.015 --> 00:10:35.269
I haven't been to the library
nearly as much.

00:10:36.731 --> 00:10:37.733
[yawns]

00:10:38.735 --> 00:10:40.864
And that's how my days go by.

00:10:42.743 --> 00:10:44.454
Still no lead on a cure,
though.

00:10:45.414 --> 00:10:46.416
[gasps softly]

00:10:47.836 --> 00:10:50.550
And I haven't seen much
of Master Fitz, lately, either.

00:10:56.144 --> 00:10:58.315
Then, one day
I received a letter.

00:11:01.531 --> 00:11:02.533
Hmm.

00:11:02.908 --> 00:11:04.537
It says it's from Soldat.

00:11:05.120 --> 00:11:06.582
[RUDEUS]
Soldat Heckler.

00:11:06.707 --> 00:11:08.670
Head honcho of Stepped Leader.

00:11:08.753 --> 00:11:10.130
Blast from the past.

00:11:12.176 --> 00:11:13.178
Okay.

00:11:13.262 --> 00:11:15.391
So he's in Sharia
for a big guild meetup,

00:11:15.559 --> 00:11:17.980
and he wants to grab a bite
to eat for old times' sake,

00:11:18.063 --> 00:11:19.274
catch up a bit.

00:11:19.775 --> 00:11:20.777
[chuckles]

00:11:22.280 --> 00:11:23.198
[thud]

00:11:23.282 --> 00:11:26.288
♪

00:11:26.371 --> 00:11:27.415
[RUDEUS]
I wonder if this is what

00:11:27.498 --> 00:11:28.668
it feels like to reconnect

00:11:28.751 --> 00:11:30.714
with your old high school
buddies, or something.

00:11:31.507 --> 00:11:32.968
Gotta say, it ain't bad.

00:11:33.051 --> 00:11:34.178
[indistinct chatter]

00:11:34.262 --> 00:11:36.057
How ya doin', Quagmire?

00:11:36.141 --> 00:11:37.894
I haven't seen you
in ages, man.

00:11:38.103 --> 00:11:40.609
Yeah, it almost feels like
a whole lifetime ago.

00:11:40.734 --> 00:11:42.529
Ya gotta get rid
of the baby clothes,

00:11:42.613 --> 00:11:44.909
you look like a run-of-the-mill
rookie in that getup.

00:11:45.034 --> 00:11:46.621
[all laugh]

00:11:46.704 --> 00:11:48.583
[RUDEUS] Maybe I miss
those days and I wanna go back.

00:11:48.666 --> 00:11:50.377
Gimme your bag,
lemme carry it somewhere.

00:11:50.461 --> 00:11:52.298
[SOLDAT]
You? Carrying our bags?

00:11:52.465 --> 00:11:55.304
Are you nuts?
We oughtta be carrying yours.

00:11:55.387 --> 00:11:57.643
[RUDEUS] You did after that
stray dragon fight, we're good.

00:11:57.726 --> 00:12:00.105
Man, we made out
like bandits on that one.

00:12:00.397 --> 00:12:01.358
[chuckles]

00:12:01.441 --> 00:12:02.611
Anyway, what's up with you,

00:12:02.694 --> 00:12:03.487
-elf ears?
-Hmm?

00:12:03.571 --> 00:12:05.909
What's a mega-slut like you
doing with a boyfriend?

00:12:05.992 --> 00:12:07.370
Is this a joke or somethin'?

00:12:07.746 --> 00:12:10.209
No, merely proof that no man
I've ever met

00:12:10.292 --> 00:12:12.046
has truly won my heart before.

00:12:13.048 --> 00:12:14.384
But now.

00:12:14.467 --> 00:12:15.804
[indistinct chatter]

00:12:15.887 --> 00:12:17.766
I've found
the man of my dreams,

00:12:17.849 --> 00:12:19.477
and I couldn't be happier.

00:12:19.603 --> 00:12:21.439
You may find it hard
to believe.

00:12:21.565 --> 00:12:22.985
But I can be quite devoted.

00:12:23.068 --> 00:12:26.074
[all laugh]

00:12:26.659 --> 00:12:30.249
-No way, that's how it went?
-Hey, Sol. Interparty meeting.

00:12:30.499 --> 00:12:31.836
Another, are you kidding me?

00:12:31.919 --> 00:12:33.548
We talked all morning,
didn't we?

00:12:33.631 --> 00:12:34.758
[KONRAD]
What do you expect?

00:12:34.842 --> 00:12:36.344
The whole clan's fired up.

00:12:36.428 --> 00:12:38.056
Might as well
get it out of the way.

00:12:38.181 --> 00:12:39.434
[groans]

00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:42.774
And here I thought I would get
to enjoy myself this afternoon.

00:12:42.858 --> 00:12:44.778
Sorry, Quagmire, I gotta run.

00:12:44.862 --> 00:12:46.532
But let's do this again,
all right?

00:12:46.615 --> 00:12:47.576
Yeah!

00:12:47.659 --> 00:12:49.287
Just let me know
when you're in town.

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:50.372
Hmm.

00:12:50.456 --> 00:12:53.462
♪

00:12:53.755 --> 00:12:54.798
[feeble bump]

00:12:57.386 --> 00:12:58.430
[RUDEUS] So, what now?

00:12:58.514 --> 00:13:00.685
You two have anything planned
for the rest of the day?

00:13:01.144 --> 00:13:02.606
[ELINALISE]
Not really, no.

00:13:03.231 --> 00:13:05.319
But actually,
we were talking about

00:13:05.402 --> 00:13:07.574
giving Cliff a crash course
in adventuring.

00:13:07.741 --> 00:13:09.160
If you would care to join us?

00:13:09.243 --> 00:13:10.245
[RUDEUS]
Uh...

00:13:10.412 --> 00:13:11.665
You needn't come.

00:13:11.957 --> 00:13:13.878
I don't intend to rely
on your help.

00:13:14.086 --> 00:13:15.089
[stunned sigh]

00:13:15.297 --> 00:13:17.677
In that case, I'll just
head on back to school.

00:13:17.886 --> 00:13:19.388
Then do take care going back,

00:13:19.472 --> 00:13:21.351
and please give
everyone our best.

00:13:21.434 --> 00:13:22.979
And, I know you know this,

00:13:23.105 --> 00:13:25.150
but please remember that
you have a beginner with you,

00:13:25.234 --> 00:13:27.238
so don't go anywhere
too dangerous.

00:13:27.488 --> 00:13:28.406
Cool?

00:13:28.490 --> 00:13:30.327
-[both] Sure thing!
-[CLIFF] Excuse me!

00:13:30.494 --> 00:13:32.039
-[RUDEUS] Wha!
-[clears throat]

00:13:32.248 --> 00:13:33.960
Yes, Rudeus, we'll be careful.

00:13:34.252 --> 00:13:36.632
No challenging dragons
or Demon Kings.

00:13:37.007 --> 00:13:37.968
[titters]

00:13:39.220 --> 00:13:42.226
[indistinct chatter]

00:13:43.436 --> 00:13:44.438
[gasps feebly]

00:13:47.821 --> 00:13:48.823
Hmm.

00:13:56.881 --> 00:13:57.883
Hey.

00:14:02.099 --> 00:14:03.728
[RUDEUS] Should
the two of them be out here?

00:14:04.771 --> 00:14:06.274
Who's guarding the princess?

00:14:07.109 --> 00:14:09.113
Well, I'd better
at least say hi.

00:14:09.196 --> 00:14:10.617
[indistinct chatter]

00:14:10.700 --> 00:14:11.869
Hey, you two!

00:14:12.453 --> 00:14:14.081
Fancy meeting you
all the way out here.

00:14:14.415 --> 00:14:15.627
Who do you...

00:14:15.710 --> 00:14:16.921
Oh, great, it's you.

00:14:17.714 --> 00:14:18.633
[RUDEUS]
Sounds like he still

00:14:18.799 --> 00:14:20.177
doesn't like me very much.

00:14:20.678 --> 00:14:21.722
But as long as I can stay

00:14:21.805 --> 00:14:23.726
friends with Master Fitz,
who cares?

00:14:24.728 --> 00:14:25.730
What's up?

00:14:25.813 --> 00:14:27.232
You okay, Master Fitz?

00:14:27.399 --> 00:14:29.655
There's something different
about you today.

00:14:30.782 --> 00:14:32.368
[RUDEUS] I can't
put my finger on it.

00:14:32.702 --> 00:14:34.372
The way he carries himself?

00:14:35.457 --> 00:14:36.502
What do you need?

00:14:36.669 --> 00:14:38.506
Speak your piece
and move along, would you?

00:14:38.881 --> 00:14:40.467
[RUDEUS]
Did I catch them at a bad time?

00:14:41.260 --> 00:14:42.429
Don't tell me.

00:14:42.806 --> 00:14:43.891
Are they on a date?

00:14:44.392 --> 00:14:46.897
Yeah, maybe Luke
swings both ways,

00:14:47.064 --> 00:14:50.320
and he and Fitz have,
uh, "sparring practice."

00:14:50.655 --> 00:14:52.449
[RUDEUS]
I just happened to see you,

00:14:52.534 --> 00:14:54.078
so I thought I would say hello.

00:14:54.913 --> 00:14:57.001
Um... Master Fitz?

00:14:59.631 --> 00:15:00.591
[stutters]
Uh...

00:15:00.675 --> 00:15:02.846
[LUKE] I see.
We appreciate the greeting.

00:15:03.096 --> 00:15:05.560
I have to remind you, however,
that Fitz isn't permitted

00:15:05.643 --> 00:15:07.479
to speak while guarding
Her Highness.

00:15:07.814 --> 00:15:08.816
Apologies.

00:15:08.899 --> 00:15:10.152
I'm sure you understand.

00:15:10.611 --> 00:15:11.739
[RUDEUS]
I guess I really did come

00:15:11.822 --> 00:15:12.824
at a bad time.

00:15:13.450 --> 00:15:15.287
Still, it seems harsh for him

00:15:15.370 --> 00:15:17.374
to ignore me
completely like this.

00:15:20.005 --> 00:15:21.007
[gasps]

00:15:22.092 --> 00:15:23.094
What is it?

00:15:23.470 --> 00:15:25.015
Oh, i-it's nothing.

00:15:25.223 --> 00:15:26.685
Um...
Excuse me.

00:15:29.398 --> 00:15:32.362
[indistinct chatter]

00:15:32.446 --> 00:15:33.532
[RUDEUS]
I don't think I let anything

00:15:33.616 --> 00:15:36.789
show on the outside,
but... man, that really stung.

00:15:38.667 --> 00:15:40.128
Why would he shun me like that?

00:15:41.047 --> 00:15:43.301
It hurts so much I can hardly
even think straight.

00:15:44.721 --> 00:15:47.727
♪

00:15:52.402 --> 00:15:53.823
[RUDEUS]
I've been mulling it over.

00:15:54.365 --> 00:15:55.660
But I still can't figure out

00:15:55.743 --> 00:15:57.997
why Master Fitz
was avoiding me just now.

00:15:59.041 --> 00:16:01.212
I don't remember doing
anything to offend him.

00:16:01.797 --> 00:16:04.176
I just wanna talk about
my feelings with someone.

00:16:04.426 --> 00:16:06.264
Well, no, I just want to gripe.

00:16:06.723 --> 00:16:07.892
I'm pretty sure Zanoba

00:16:07.976 --> 00:16:09.353
is at the Mages' Guild
right now

00:16:09.436 --> 00:16:11.023
for some
Blessed Child research.

00:16:12.317 --> 00:16:13.904
He probably took Julie
with him.

00:16:14.614 --> 00:16:16.409
Now, Linia and Pursena,

00:16:16.743 --> 00:16:20.333
would be terrible listeners,
prob'ly make fun of me.

00:16:21.920 --> 00:16:23.591
And Nanahoshi...
[sighs]

00:16:23.674 --> 00:16:25.511
kind of has her hands full.

00:16:25.845 --> 00:16:27.682
She won't wanna listen
to my problems.

00:16:28.642 --> 00:16:31.355
[water trickling]

00:16:31.439 --> 00:16:32.482
[sighs deeply]

00:16:32.567 --> 00:16:35.573
♪

00:16:36.909 --> 00:16:38.453
[RUDEUS]
Okay. Whatever.

00:16:38.621 --> 00:16:40.207
Might as well go
to the library.

00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:45.383
[footsteps approaching]

00:16:48.139 --> 00:16:49.141
-Oh, hey.
-Uh!

00:16:49.433 --> 00:16:51.479
[gasping excitedly]
Hey, Rudeus.

00:16:51.772 --> 00:16:53.316
Been a little while, hasn't it?

00:16:53.776 --> 00:16:56.197
[RUDEUS]
He's just his normal self.

00:16:56.364 --> 00:16:57.575
Is there a problem?

00:16:57.992 --> 00:16:59.537
Do I have something
on my face?

00:16:59.621 --> 00:17:00.831
[chair sliding]

00:17:00.915 --> 00:17:03.336
Why did you ignore me
in the market earlier today?!

00:17:03.545 --> 00:17:04.547
[gasps]

00:17:05.675 --> 00:17:06.593
I'm sorry.

00:17:06.677 --> 00:17:08.931
But it really is true
that I'm not allowed to speak

00:17:09.014 --> 00:17:10.308
while I'm on duty, you know.

00:17:10.518 --> 00:17:11.895
"Silent" Fitz.

00:17:12.396 --> 00:17:15.026
People don't take me seriously
because of my voice...

00:17:15.569 --> 00:17:16.571
it's "childish".

00:17:16.905 --> 00:17:19.076
So in public,
I'm not supposed to speak.

00:17:19.493 --> 00:17:21.330
Especially
around Princess Ariel.

00:17:21.790 --> 00:17:23.752
Okay, but I didn't see

00:17:23.836 --> 00:17:25.213
the princess
anywhere around you.

00:17:26.090 --> 00:17:27.885
[FITZ]
She was in a shop nearby.

00:17:28.177 --> 00:17:29.848
We aren't her only protection.

00:17:30.223 --> 00:17:31.225
[sighs]

00:17:33.522 --> 00:17:35.483
Forgive me for demanding
your attention, then.

00:17:36.152 --> 00:17:37.446
Poor timing, I guess.

00:17:37.530 --> 00:17:38.574
Mm-mm.

00:17:38.657 --> 00:17:39.659
It's all right.

00:17:40.076 --> 00:17:42.456
I feel bad that I couldn't
respond to you, though.

00:17:44.043 --> 00:17:45.128
[RUDEUS]
Okay, I think I see

00:17:45.211 --> 00:17:46.255
what's happening here.

00:17:46.965 --> 00:17:50.055
I'm not positive,
but I think Princess Ariel

00:17:50.138 --> 00:17:53.394
has actually been disguising
herself as Master Fitz somehow.

00:17:53.604 --> 00:17:55.482
So she was trying
to avoid me earlier

00:17:55.566 --> 00:17:57.987
because any careless chitchat
could blow her cover.

00:17:58.781 --> 00:17:59.699
The more I think about it,

00:17:59.783 --> 00:18:01.452
the more sense
it makes overall.

00:18:02.204 --> 00:18:04.500
But either way,
there's still no evidence

00:18:04.584 --> 00:18:05.711
that Fitz is mad at me.

00:18:06.337 --> 00:18:07.965
And that's all
I really care about.

00:18:08.341 --> 00:18:09.301
So, good.

00:18:10.303 --> 00:18:11.598
Well, that's a relief.

00:18:12.015 --> 00:18:13.184
I was starting to worry

00:18:13.267 --> 00:18:15.355
that you suddenly started
hating me or something.

00:18:15.523 --> 00:18:16.608
[laughs]

00:18:16.942 --> 00:18:19.823
No, of course not,
how could I ever hate you?

00:18:20.323 --> 00:18:21.325
[exhales]

00:18:22.244 --> 00:18:25.250
♪

00:18:26.962 --> 00:18:28.381
[feeble crackling]

00:18:29.299 --> 00:18:30.301
[gasps]

00:18:31.137 --> 00:18:33.600
♪

00:18:33.684 --> 00:18:34.936
[sighing and sobbing]

00:18:36.063 --> 00:18:37.274
[RUDEUS]
Every little thing he does

00:18:37.357 --> 00:18:38.569
sticks with me.

00:18:38.986 --> 00:18:40.948
The way he scratches
behind his ears.

00:18:41.616 --> 00:18:44.079
The way he stretches when
he finishes a study session.

00:18:45.165 --> 00:18:47.377
The way he smells
when he brushes close by me.

00:18:47.461 --> 00:18:49.381
♪

00:18:49.465 --> 00:18:51.051
And then there's that smile.

00:18:51.845 --> 00:18:54.475
I can't get that bashful smile
out of my head.

00:18:54.559 --> 00:18:56.730
♪

00:18:56.813 --> 00:18:59.819
[indistinct chatter]

00:19:07.459 --> 00:19:10.006
[RUDEUS] I know
what all this means, of course.

00:19:11.175 --> 00:19:12.177
[gasps]

00:19:12.803 --> 00:19:13.889
[flustered stuttering]

00:19:14.014 --> 00:19:15.099
[RUDEUS]
I'm in love.

00:19:15.183 --> 00:19:18.189
♪

00:19:19.483 --> 00:19:20.485
Hmm?

00:19:20.569 --> 00:19:23.449
♪

00:19:23.534 --> 00:19:24.536
[sighs]

00:19:25.119 --> 00:19:26.665
[RUDEUS]
I'm in love with a man.

00:19:27.834 --> 00:19:30.631
Assuming he really is one,
which... hmm...

00:19:33.679 --> 00:19:34.556
[door opens]

00:19:34.639 --> 00:19:36.267
-[RUDEUS] Professor Jenius?
-Hmm?

00:19:36.893 --> 00:19:38.354
Well, hello, Rudeus.

00:19:38.689 --> 00:19:40.233
What brings you
to see me today?

00:19:40.901 --> 00:19:44.408
Well, I want to ask
about Master Fitz.

00:19:46.663 --> 00:19:47.665
[sighs]

00:19:49.961 --> 00:19:51.338
Then you'll have to forgive me.

00:19:51.715 --> 00:19:53.927
The staff have been given
rather strict instruction

00:19:54.011 --> 00:19:55.723
regarding him and his employer.

00:19:56.098 --> 00:19:57.518
I see, of course.

00:19:58.269 --> 00:19:59.229
Could you confirm

00:19:59.313 --> 00:20:01.610
basic information for me,
like his sex?

00:20:01.818 --> 00:20:03.822
Like his sex?
Well, yes.

00:20:04.699 --> 00:20:05.701
Mm.

00:20:06.452 --> 00:20:07.454
[gulps]

00:20:08.456 --> 00:20:10.628
Silent Fitz... is male.

00:20:14.217 --> 00:20:15.303
[RUDEUS]
Well, that was pretty

00:20:15.386 --> 00:20:16.305
unconvincing.

00:20:16.806 --> 00:20:17.683
And what was that about

00:20:17.767 --> 00:20:20.104
"strict instruction regarding"
Fitz?

00:20:24.781 --> 00:20:25.741
[sighs]

00:20:25.824 --> 00:20:28.329
What would I do if he actually
turned out to be a woman?

00:20:29.122 --> 00:20:30.333
Would I ask him out?

00:20:31.043 --> 00:20:33.047
Wish I could at least
jerk off about it.

00:20:34.257 --> 00:20:35.426
Uh!

00:20:35.594 --> 00:20:37.890
-[gasps]
-Sorry, what'd you say?

00:20:38.307 --> 00:20:40.019
-Aah! -Watch out!
-[RUDEUS grunts]

00:20:40.478 --> 00:20:42.315
Aah!
[both grunt]

00:20:42.399 --> 00:20:43.401
[clattering]

00:20:47.117 --> 00:20:48.912
[breathes shakily]

00:20:49.831 --> 00:20:50.833
[breathes shakily]

00:20:58.180 --> 00:20:59.182
Uh...

00:20:59.433 --> 00:21:01.395
I...
I-I'm so sorry.

00:21:02.188 --> 00:21:05.612
Master Fitz, could it be
that you're actually a woman?

00:21:05.696 --> 00:21:06.698
[gasps]

00:21:07.282 --> 00:21:08.492
[breathes shakily]

00:21:08.618 --> 00:21:09.453
[shakily speaking]
Mm-mm.

00:21:09.537 --> 00:21:11.290
N-No!
You're mistaken.

00:21:11.666 --> 00:21:13.837
I... I'm a man!

00:21:14.004 --> 00:21:14.881
[sobs]
[running footsteps]

00:21:15.214 --> 00:21:16.926
[RUDEUS]
Master Fitz is a woman.

00:21:17.343 --> 00:21:18.471
That's a big deal.

00:21:19.347 --> 00:21:21.143
But even more importantly...

00:21:22.312 --> 00:21:23.439
[RUDEUS]
I got a boner.

00:21:24.609 --> 00:21:25.569
Amazing.

00:21:25.652 --> 00:21:27.071
[RUDEUS]
I can't believe it!

00:21:27.280 --> 00:21:28.157
All because I came

00:21:28.240 --> 00:21:30.036
to investigate
the mana disaster.

00:21:30.704 --> 00:21:32.541
Thank you, Lord Man-God!

00:21:32.750 --> 00:21:35.631
Although, Fitz obviously
wants to be known as a man.

00:21:36.298 --> 00:21:37.217
[RUDEUS]
Well, fine!

00:21:37.425 --> 00:21:40.014
He...
She has done so much for me,

00:21:40.098 --> 00:21:41.433
I can't betray that.

00:21:41.518 --> 00:21:43.980
I have a responsibility
to respect her wishes

00:21:44.064 --> 00:21:46.528
and help her keep up the act
for however long she wants.

00:21:46.945 --> 00:21:49.742
Master Fitz definitely holds
the key to curing my ED,

00:21:50.409 --> 00:21:52.413
but I can't get any more
intimate with him now.

00:21:52.748 --> 00:21:53.750
Maybe soon.

00:21:54.794 --> 00:21:55.796
Hey.

00:21:56.840 --> 00:21:59.846
[breathing coarsely]

00:22:00.054 --> 00:22:02.518
I guess this cure
still has a long way to go.

00:22:02.977 --> 00:22:03.979
[sighs]

00:22:04.062 --> 00:22:04.897
Oh, well...

00:22:05.273 --> 00:22:06.651
I can see my way forward.

00:22:06.901 --> 00:22:08.028
So why rush?

